# Server Development Guide

Comprehensive guide for Express 5, TypeORM, API design, and backend patterns.

---

## 1. Express 5 Patterns

### Route Structure

```
packages/server/src/
├── api/
│   ├── index.ts              # createApp() -- Express app setup, middleware, route registration
│   ├── middleware/
│   │   ├── errorHandler.ts   # Global error handler
│   │   └── validate.ts       # Zod validateBody middleware
│   └── routes/
│       ├── launches.ts       # GET /api/launches, /api/launches/report, /api/launches/trends
│       ├── testItems.ts      # GET /api/test-items/launch/:id
│       ├── triage.ts         # POST /api/triage/:itemId, /api/triage/bulk
│       └── ...               # One file per resource
├── clients/                  # External API clients (RP, Jira, Jenkins)
├── db/
│   ├── entities/             # TypeORM entities
│   ├── migrations/           # TypeORM migrations
│   └── store/                # Data access layer (queries, CRUD)
├── notifiers/                # Slack, email notification senders
├── pipeline/                 # Data ingestion pipeline (phases, manager)
├── services/                 # Business logic services
└── utils/                    # Shared server utilities
```

### Route Handler Pattern

```typescript
router.get('/:id', async (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
  try {
    const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
    if (Number.isNaN(id)) {
      res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid ID' });
      return;
    }
    const data = await store.getById(id);
    if (!data) {
      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });
      return;
    }
    res.json(data);
  } catch (err) {
    next(err);
  }
});
```

Rules:
- ALWAYS wrap async handlers in try/catch with `next(err)`
- Validate path params (parseInt, check NaN)
- Return early on validation failures (400) and not-found (404)
- Use `validateBody(schema)` middleware on ALL POST/PUT routes
- Keep handlers thin: delegate to store/service layer

### Middleware Chain

```
helmet() → cors() → express.json() → pinoHttp() → routes → errorHandler
```

- `helmet`: security headers
- `cors`: cross-origin configuration
- `express.json()`: body parsing with size limit
- `pinoHttp`: structured request logging
- `errorHandler`: catches all unhandled errors, returns 500

