## 3. API Design

### REST Conventions

| Method | Purpose | Status Codes |
|--------|---------|-------------|
| GET | Read data | 200, 400, 404, 500 |
| POST | Create or mutate | 200/201, 400, 500 |
| PUT | Full update | 200, 400, 404, 500 |
| DELETE | Remove | 200/204, 404, 500 |

### Response Shapes

```typescript
// Success
res.json(data);                    // Direct data
res.json({ items, total, page }); // Paginated

// Error
res.status(400).json({ error: 'Validation failed', details: [...] });
res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });
res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
```

### Validation

```typescript
import { validateBody } from '../middleware/validate';
import { TriageRequestSchema } from '@cnv-monitor/shared';

router.post('/:itemId', validateBody(TriageRequestSchema), async (req, res, next) => {
  // req.body is validated and typed
});
```

- ALL POST routes MUST use `validateBody(schema)`
- Schemas live in `@cnv-monitor/shared`
- Validation errors return 400 with field-level details

