## 6. Pipeline Architecture

### Phase Design

```
FetchLaunches → FetchItems → EnrichJenkins
```

- Each phase implements a standard interface: `estimate()`, `execute()`, `retryItem()`
- Progress reported via WebSocket to connected clients
- Errors in one item don't stop the entire phase
- Failed items can be retried individually
- Pipeline can be cancelled mid-phase

### Error Recovery

- Per-item error handling (don't fail the entire batch)
- Failed items logged with context for debugging
- Retry mechanism with exponential backoff for transient failures
- Pipeline state persisted for resume after crash

---

## 7. Security (Server-specific)

- `helmet()` middleware for security headers
- `express-rate-limit` on mutation endpoints
- Input validation via Zod on all POST routes
- Parameterized SQL queries (no string interpolation)
- Environment variables for all secrets
- No sensitive data in error responses or logs
- CORS configured for production origins
